<TEXT>
marcus eliason london news editor for the 
associated press since 1988 has been named the aps bureau chief 
in jerusalem 
the appointment was announced tuesday by ap president louis d 
boccardi 
eliason 43 succeeds nicolas b tatro who is on leave as a 
journalism fellow sponsored by the national endowment for the 
humanities at the university of michigan 
eliason joined the ap in tel aviv in 1968 and worked in israel 
for 14 years including assignments as jerusalem correspondent and 
tel aviv news editor he also worked for the ap in paris from 1978 
to 1980 and in london since 1984 
eliason a native of port elizabeth south africa was a 
reporter for the jerusalem post before joining the ap 
