<TEXT>
a small 3500yearold pottery hippopotamus has 
sold for 955600 a record auction price for an egyptian antiquity 
the 425 inchlong hippo is glazed in turquoise and has lotus 
blossoms and a grasshopper painted on its back 
sothebys auctioneers said only six others like it are known 
london dealer robin symes bought the artifact on tuesday it was 
sold by antoinette schuster a descendant of the late marion 
schuster a swiss collector 
the previous top price for an egyptian antiquity was 742500 
for a granite figure of the goddess sekhmet auctioned in 1986 
the hippo was found in 1907 at abydos by john garstang an 
english archaeologist it was later owned by a clergyman the rev 
william macgregor who had paid 100 pounds then 500 to become 
one of 10 patrons of the excavation 
hippos appear only in tombs of the middle kingdom period between 
2040 and 1650 bc and their purpose is not known 
some scholars believe they symbolize rebirth or that they were 
simply intended to give pleasure in the afterlife 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

