with the states gop hierarchy 
he says he bolted the republican party because 20 years of 
trying to lead by example didnt work 
if i was going to run for governor it wasnt going to be a 
philosophical debate with the republicans weicker said ive 
had that what i wanted to spend my time on was the state of 
connecticut 
weickers candidacy seems to be hurting rowland the most the 
former senator has picked up endorsements from several prominent 
republicans including mary boatwright a member of the republican 
national committee 
a recent weicker fundraiser in washington featured some of his 
former senate colleagues from both sides of the aisle including 
former gop senators paul laxalt of nevada and edward brooke of 
massachusetts and incumbent democrat tom harkin of iowa 
morrison and rowland both say they could spend 4 million or 
more on the race weicker who doesnt face the traditional need to 
court delegates and who has no need to boost his name recognition 
hopes to get away with half as much 
ferrees most recent poll had weicker favored by 41 percent of 
those surveyed rowland with 11 percent and morrison with 9 percent 
