described as environmental and safety concerns 
in a fiveyear environmental cleanup plan issued last week the 
department said the plant is needed to dispose of hanfords 
remaining nuclear fuel rods 
the plant known as purex is a nuclear reprocessing facility 
that extracts plutonium and uranium from the used rods for use in 
nuclear weapons and research 
approximately 2100 tons of highly radioactive used rods are now 
stored in pools of water on the hanford reservation and some are 
leaking radioactivity into the water the environmental group said 
saying that plutonium production at purex is needed for 
