the organization said storing the rods under a dry inert gas 
such as helium or argon might be the safest way to handle them 
until a longterm disposal plan is worked out 
failing this the study said storage in capsules in water 
basins is likely to be preferable on environmental grounds to 
the existing plan 
it is true that the existing situation with hanfords used 
nuclear fuels is a real mess but that is largely because doe 
ignored the situation and let the problem fester instead of 
encapsulating the leaking fuel a decade ago saleska said 
