in december the board gave harris until jan 31 to renew his 
state superintendents certificate which he did he also was 
criticized for failing to disclose that an assistant superintendent 
had been accused of plagiarizing a doctoral dissertation 
in march he was questioned by the board for spending 400000 
on consulting fees during a sixmonth period 
the board regrets the need to take this action but has 
concluded a change in leadership must be made glover said in a 
statement the school system has not had the sense of teamwork 
which is necessary to achieve and sustain progress and there has 
not been a good working relationship between the board and the 
superintendent based on mutual trust and cooperation 
</TEXT>
