only alleged that secretary of state natalie meyer improperly 
allowed backers of official english to collect new petition 
signatures after failing to present enough valid ones by deadline 
but meyer barred opponents from challenging the new signatures 
saying the challenge wasnt timely the lawsuit said 
the high court on monday ruled 63 that state regulations 
affecting voter initiatives should be read liberally to prevent 
thwarting the publics right to create laws 
the law which was approved by 64 percent of voters amended the 
colorado constitution to declare english the states official 
language sixteen other states have similar laws 
proponents of the law said their main goal was to force the 
government to use english but the governor of colorado and mayor 
of denver issued executive orders allowing the government to 
provide official information such as voting regulations in 
