<TEXT>
a television reporter told a judge the name 
of a confidential source today and was immediately freed from the 
jail where he had served two weeks of a sixmonth contempt of court 
sentence 
i want to see my wife and my son and have a pizza and beer 
said kmol reporter brian karem moments after he was freed by state 
district judge pat priest 
karem was jailed june 27 for refusing to say who arranged a 
telephone interview with jailed capital murder suspect henry 
hernandez hernandez and his brother julian are charged in the 
march 1989 shooting death of a san antonio police officer gary 
williams 
karem today identified the source as deborah ledesma a cousin 
of the hernandez brothers 
he said he decided to reveal the name after ms ledesma who now 
lives in california agreed to relieve him of his promise to 
protect her identity 
during todays hearing priest asked karem about the extent of 
ms ledesmas involvement when told she had simply arranged the 
interview priest said i dont understand then what would be 
the need for anonymity on her part she never had anything to 
do with the statements that you ran on the air is that correct 
karem replied yes then priest said he is released 
karems attorney larry macon said he and other lawyers 
obtained a telephone deposition monday night from ms ledesma who 
has been living in santa clara calif since may 1989 
in the deposition the woman confirmed that she helped arrange a 
threeway telephone conversation that also involved karem and henry 
hernandez macon said 
attorneys in the murder trial of the hernandez brothers have 
said they need to know who arranged the interview to assure a fair 
trial and determine whether the interview should be admitted as 
evidence 
henry hernandez said in the interview that he shot the officer 
in selfdefense 
in a telephone interview carried live by kmol monday night 
karem indicated he would be out of jail soon and contended that 
the defense has known for some time who the source was 
im kind of upset that it took 13 months for the district 
attorney and the defense to do their job theyve been playing a 
game he said 
earlier monday the supreme court voted 72 to reject karems 
emergency request that he be freed pending his appeal of the 
judges contempt order that led to his jailing 
