<TEXT>
state water officials are searching 
for the cause of a fish kill in a river behind an arco chemical co 
plant where 17 workers died last week in an explosion and fire 
although an exact count had not been completed texas water 
commission spokesman bill colbert said quite a few fish were 
noticed drifting in the water or along the shore near bear lake an 
inlet of that river 
colbert said monday the commission was awaiting test results of 
water samples from the san jacinto river to determine the cause of 
the fish kill 
but preliminary tests pointed to a combination of factors 
including a sudden change in water temperatures and the possibility 
of caustic substances such as firefighting foam in the water 
first reports of the kill came several hours after a fire and 
explosion late thursday decimated an area the size of a city block 
at the plant colbert said and a field evaluation was initiated 
the next day 
