<TEXT>
an 80yearold man serving a life 
sentence for shooting his ailing wife to death has been moved to a 
tougher prison as part of a general crackdown on prison security 
roswell gilbert whose mercy killing defense after the march 
1985 shooting drew widespread publicity was moved from the medium 
security lawtey correctional facility to a top security prison at 
lake butler said h edward sands assistant superintendent at 
lawtey 
last month donald dillbeck serving a mandatory life sentence 
in the murder of a policeman walked away from a workrelease 
program and was charged with killing a shopper outside a 
tallahassee mall 
in response gov bob martinez ordered inmates who are serving a 
type of sentence that rules out early parole to be put in 
topsecurity prisons among them was gilbert 
his attorney bradley stark said gilberts health could be 
endangered by the stress of moving to another prison 
its pretty clear to me roswell gilbert shouldnt be in 
prison and secondly if he is going to be in prison he shouldnt 
be in maximum security stark said 
gilbert suffers from lung and heart diseases and has undergone 
surgery for bladder and urinary tract infections since he was 
imprisoned stark said 
on march 4 1985 gilbert a retired engineer shot and killed 
his wife emily in what he said was act of love a mercy killing 
to end her suffering from alzheimers disease he was convicted of 
firstdegree murder and sentenced to life in prison with a minimum 
of 25 years in prison 
his case was dramatized in a madefortelevision movie 
