return home bernardi said 
bernardi who said he was a frequent traveler to tirana said 
the capitals streets appeared peaceful away from the embassy 
district 
albanias communist leader ramiz alia began this year to 
institute some economic reforms in the nation of 32 million and 
sought to establish limited ties with other countries 
for 45 years travel for average albanians has been virtually 
impossible but a package of new regulations entitles all albanians 
over age 16 to have a passport 
