<TEXT>
vernon grant creator of the kelloggs 
cereal characters snap crackle and pop and a longtime magazine and 
book illustrator has died he was 88 
he died monday at a nursing home where he had been for several 
weeks 
he was right up there with norman rockwell in the number of 
covers he designed said linda williams chairwoman of the vernon 
grantart advisory committee with the museum of york county 
the nursing home would not release a cause of death but ms 
williams said he had been in declining health since he broke his 
hip some months ago 
grant was born in nebraska in 1902 and moved with his family to 
california when he was a teenager he studied at the university of 
southern california and later at the art institute of chicago 
in 1932 a gnome figure he drew of santa claus landed on the 
cover of ladies home journal and was a smashing success 
a year later inspired by a radio commercial for kelloggs rice 
krispies he created the gnomelike characters of snap crackle and 
pop he submitted drawings to the companys ad agency 
overall he designed 187 magazine covers from the 1930s to the 
50s and illustrated childrens books 
in 1947 grant and his wife elizabeth moved to her hometown of 
rock hill to raise their family and farm 600 acres while living in 
south carolina he developed a strain of grass and became known for 
his conservation methods 
grant is survived by his wife a son and a daughter 
</TEXT>
