an asteroid hurtled across earths orbit 
at a distance of only 3 million miles tuesday a close encounter 
on the astronomical scale planetary scientists said 
the asteroid dubbed 1990 mf made one of the closer crossings 
of earth orbit observed in the last 50 years it had been tracked 
since jet propulsion laboratory planetary scientist eleanor helin 
discovered it on june 26 
the rocky objects diameter was estimated at 300 feet to 1000 
feet and it was projected to have accelerated to 22000 mph at its 
closest approach 
helin head of the palomar planetcrossing asteroid survey said 
there are a dozen asteroids that are considered to have come 
relatively close 
the closest was last year when an asteroid passed at a distance 
of 460000 to 480000 miles from earth an earlier one was just 
under 500000 miles the 1990 mf asteroid is among 10 in the 3 
millionmile range 
these are all close encounters astronomically helin said 
