imprisoned extremist lyndon larouche and his 
followers are running in scores of primary and general election 
races this year as they try to regroup politically after a string 
of legal defeats 
larouche followers stunned and embarrassed the democratic party 
in 1986 by winning primary nominations for two statewide offices in 
