<DOCNO> AP900710-0190 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the look of the wheeling symphony 
orchestra strikes a distinctive chord but its improved sound 
proves that classical music can have no sex 
its conductor for more than four years rachael worby is one of 
few women comma 
its kind of like having a handful of electricity said ron 
hobbs a wheeling symphony orchestra director she has that sense 
of excitement that is around her all the time 
nding the baton we dont consider her a female conductor shes a 
conductor 
with talent who just happens to be female said agnes 
eisenberger her agent she caught our attention primarily 
because of her talent and ability to get her musical message 
across 
worby 41 also has caught the renewed attention of west 
virginia when she was publicly courted by gov gaston caperton 
they married on may 25 
but long before she became west virginias first lady she 
helped double the wheeling orchestras budget and nearly triple its 
season ticket sales in the same theater that is home to country 
musics jamboree usa radio program 
she also is music director of the young peoples concerts at 
carnegie hall one of lalent teaching 
children about music as exceptional 
at one session with a group of children it was almost like 
they were watching a magician hobbs said 
symphony members agree 
a lot of conductors tend to keep a lot of distance between 
themselves and their orchestra members its kind of the old 
european style of dictator and peon said larry bradford viola 
principal shes not like that at all 
she can be your friend off the podium said carolyn wann 
wheelings associate concertmaster 
worbys love for music stems from a childhood in nyack ny 
filled with culture and music and an idolatry of bernstein 
here was a man who was conducting brahms at lincoln center 
writing west side story and conducting the young peoples 
concerts at carnegie hall worby said he couldnt be 
pigeonholed he was whatever he wanted to be he was eclectic in 
his musical tastes and in addition to that he really stands by 
his principles 
worby who has been called sort of a female leonard 
bernstein also is musically eclectic she loves country music 
and was the lead singer in ragnarock and the fly boys a rock group 
she was the product of two sets of grandparents dramatically 
different in style but equally committed to music and the arts 
when my mothers parents wanted to do something with me very 
special they took me to the threepenny opera i was 9 maybe 10 
maybe younger when my fathers parents wanted to take me some 
place special they took me to radio city music hall to see the 
rockettes 
her father a hardware manufacturer cant read music but louis 
worby can sing and he plays piano from the letters written above 
notes in music books 
there wasnt a night when my father wouldnt go after dinner 
to sit at the piano and sing cole porter george gershwin irving 
berlin worby said he would teach me very simple melodies 
and we would sing it over and over again and suddenly he would 
start singing harmony 
her maternal grandfather also sang to her but in a different 
way 
i very clearly remember my grandfather had a red wheelbarrow 
which he would put me in and wheel me around in a small wooded area 
in the back of the house she said 
while he was wheeling me around he would hum melodies of 
brahms symphonies to me with his russian accent in english if 
youre humming its la la lah la la lah my grandfather it was 
tee rah ruhmmmm tee rah ruhmmmm 
worby credits her mother who has perfect pitch with literally 
devoting a decade of her life to teaching her discipline 
diana worby a literature professor agreed her daughter was 
less than enthusiastic at times when she was 8 10 12 and 
supposed to be practicing piano she was the same as every other 
kid i dont want to practice i dont want to practice diana 
worby said 
before it seemed like every concert when she was supposed to 
perform something generally happened she got a fever or 
sprained her thumb playing softball 
her mothers discipline helped worby through her formal music 
education a bachelors degree from the state university of new 
york at potsdam graduate work at indiana university and a 
doctorate in musicology from brandeis university 
it also shows in her work now 
shes really studying a lot many conductors get to the midway 
point in their careers and they stop learning from other 
conductors other orchestras other approaches bradford said 
it takes time it takes years to peak said milutin 
lazich a bass singer who recently performed mozarts requiem 
under worbys direction there is unused potential there still 
worbys concern is to keep learning 
im a student i wont be happy until i have a sense that i 
have absorbed everything there is to absorb worby said when 
would i be finished studying beethovens fifth symphony its such 
a humbling experience to even say it beethovens fifth symphony 
in the face of it im still an infant 
worby however hasnt lost sight of her goal to be conductor of 
the greatest orchestra she can possibly lead 
i feel inside of me an inexorable forward motion she said 
ill know where the resting place is 
</TEXT>
