<TEXT>
there was a time when dan seals slept 
under a grand piano at a recording studio at night trying to 
survive after going bankrupt 
but things are a lot better for the country star who grew to 
fame in the 1970s as england dan of the pop duo england dan and 
john ford coley what helped turn around his career was the 
awardwinning bop in 1986 
nine of his last 10 single releases have reached no 1 on the 
country music charts most recently love on arrival in april 
but 10 years ago the 42yearold seals was in dire straits 
financially as the result of what he calls an oversight by a 
business associate an accountant had neglected to pay the 
employers share of federal taxes involving employees seals had on 
his payroll 
they the irs came and got it all cars record royalties 
everything seals recalled i didnt have any place to go so i 
just stayed at the studio under the grand i remember sitting 
around wondering how wed get the money for a hamburger because 
wed used up everything we had i figured id get a job at a 
filling station 
pumping gas wasnt necessary his solo career took off shortly 
thereafter and seals has been one of the steadiest country music 
singers since his first no 1 country hit everybodys dream 
girl in 1983 
his music ranges from frisky tunes such as bop to the 
wistful affection in my old yellow car and weepers such as 
everything that glitters 
his wellcrafted songs tend to be insightful and graphic with 
lofty themes his instrumentation can be adventurous he used horns 
not often heard in country music on his current album on 
arrival 
he also was daring last year in his music video rage on 
when he addressed a topic rare in country music an interracial 
relationship it showed angry youths smashing the windows of the 
car of a young man dating an oriental girl one boy hurled a beer 
bottle at the girls father 
the song itself was about small town values 
when we record songs we take chances the softspoken seals 
said in an interview ive got to the point where we are 
stretching and trying new things not to shock but just to keep 
ourselves alive and interested we feel we are on the cutting edge 
of what we can do 
seals said the video was a reflection of his bahai religious 
beliefs 
i believe mankind is one family and that all religions are 
one he said 
he and coley had the pop hit id really love to see you 
tonight which sold 2 million records in 1976 they broke up in 
1979 to pursue separate careers 
hes an actor in los angeles now seals said im real 
proud for him 
seals older brother jim was half of the pop duo seals and 
crofts whose hits in the 1970s included summer breeze and 
diamond girl seals and crofts are now putting together an 
album as a follow up to their first tour in 10 years 
dan seals who grew up in dallas was surprised at the airplay 
for bop which crossed over to the pop charts 
ive had radio people tell me that when bop was out they had 
to hire people to handle calls to the station asking to hear it 
because they didnt have time he said it was a big jazzercise 
record and a big nightclub song for clubs to play when the band 
took a break 
i thought the song wouldnt do anything because the 
synthesizers we used were too different i was wrong delighted i 
was wrong 
his other hit records include big wheels in the moonlight 
my babys got good timing you still love me i will be 
there and three time loser he and marie osmond teamed up on 
another no 1 record meet me in montana 
his 1986 album wont be blue aymore was no 1 and reached 
gold status for selling 500000 copies 
