united brands inc became chiquita brands international inc 
ohio mattress co is now known as sealy corp and ivan boesky amp co 
lp became cx partners lp 
but despite these striking examples of new company calling 
cards a survey released monday said the volume of corporate name 
changes fell 9 percent in the first half of 1990 compared with a 
year earlier 
the consulting firm anspach grossman portugal inc said the 697 
corporate names changes in the first six months of 1990 was down 
from 767 in the first half of 1989 it was the fewest changes for 
the period since there were 579 in the first half of 1986 
joel portugal a principal in the identity consulting firm said 
the decline reflected an overall decline in general business 
activity firsthalf name changes peaked at 931 in early 1988 
the latest dropoff occurred despite an increase in the number 
of name changes stemming from mergers and acquisitions 
that was the single biggest category of name change 
explanations totaling 367 changes or 53 percent of the total 
compared with 351 a year earlier 
prominent among mergerrelated changes were 61 resulting from 
governmentassisted actions related to the thrift industry 
elective name changes accounted for another 125 down from 139 a 
year earlier while divestitures accounted for 93 changes down 
from 108 
elective changes included united brands change as well as the 
switch of international minerals and chemical corp to imcera group 
and amca internationals change to united dominion industries 
other reasons included 44 due to sale of assets 34 for 
corporate restructuring seven for changes to a holding company 
configuration eight for leveraged buyouts or spinoffs and 19 for 
assorted other reasons 
portugal said companies have become more sophisticated in recent 
years about name changes 
he said two decades ago executives often would change a 
companys name in an effort to prime the pump and boost sales 
but he said modern executives make changes for substance not 
appearances sake and said the falloff in name changes this year 
may indicate that companies dont feel their business has changed 
enough to warrant a switch 
with less changes taking place in business there is less 
reason to communicate a change he said 
but he said some companies sought to disassociate themselves 
from names that became infamous in the 1980s 
