a 30day coolingoff period began today after 
contract talks between eastern airlines and the air line pilots 
association reached an impasse 
the latest round of talks started in midmay several weeks 
after a federal bankruptcy court in new york appointed martin 
shugrue as a trustee to take control of eastern from frank lorenzo 
lorenzo is chairman of continental airlines holdings inc then 
called texas air corp the parent of eastern 
after the 30day period the alpa pilots could legally vote to 
strike miamibased eastern but such a move likely would have 
little effect since most of the 1900 pilots at eastern currently 
are nonunion 
flight attendants and alpa pilots at eastern walked out in 
sympathy with the machinists union in march 1989 but called off 
their strikes last november 
most of the pilots were replaced by nonunion hires and only a 
few hundred alpa fliers remained at eastern through the strike or 
later returned to work there many former eastern pilots still are 
out of work 
an alpa strike vote would be a nonevent eastern 
spokeswoman karen ceremsak said monday in miami she said the 
company would work toward a negotiated settlement in the next 30 
days 
ej breen a member of the master executive council of alpa for 
