united technologies corp plans to build 
and manage a commercial spaceport in northern australia a move 
that would put the aerospace giant at the center of the emerging 
international spacelaunch industry 
the bush administration gave informal approval sunday to a plan 
in which a utc subsidiary usbi co of huntsville ala will 
design and develop the spaceport in cape york australia the base 
will be used to launch us satellites on sovietbuilt zenit 
rockets for telecommunications customers worldwide 
if completed utcs venture would represent the first time a 
private company has built a spaceport all previous spaceports have 
been built by government military or space agencies 
