<TEXT>
after a partial verdict in the first trial 
stemming from an fbi commodity sting operation the government 
plans to try again to prove that three traders conspired to cheat 
customers 
in addition to a racketeering charge that stumped a us 
district court jury prosecutors also plan to refile scores of 
fraud charges against the defendants 
it is our intention at this point to go forward with the 
remaining charges assistant us attorney mark pollack said 
after the jury ended 11 days of deliberations by returning verdicts 
on only 30 of 116 counts 
the panel convicted two traders on commodity fraud charges and 
acquitted a third us district judge ann c williams who 
presided over the nearly two months of proceedings declared a 
mistrial on the counts the jury didnt resolve 
robert d mosky 34 a floor broker portrayed by prosecutors as 
the leader of a fraud scheme in the mercs swiss franc futures pit 
was found guilty of seven counts of commodity exchange act fraud 
the least serious charges against him 
the jury acquitted him of 20 commodity mail and wire fraud 
charges and deadlocked on 55 other counts including a racketeering 
charge 
independent trader danny l scheck 28 was convicted of one 
count of commodity fraud the jury could not reach a verdict on 19 
other counts against scheck 
david zatz 43 another independent trader in the swiss franc 
pit was acquitted on two commodity fraud counts the jury could 
not decide 12 other counts against zatz 
each commodity fraud count carries a maximum prison sentence of 
five years and a 100000 fine prosecutors said 
the men were the first group of commodities traders to stand 
trial on charges resulting from a continuing fbi probe of 
corruption at the merc and the chicago board of trade the worlds 
biggest commodity futures markets 
two other groups 13 soybean traders from the board of trade 
and 15 japanese yen traders from the merc go on trial in 
september 
assistant us attorney james fleissner is not working on those 
cases but said their structure probably would be similar 
we have certain kinds of evidence the agent will testify 
about what he saw the people who are testifying as cooperators 
will testify about what they saw we will play tapes he said 
in all 48 people have been indicted since last august sixteen 
have pleaded guilty to reduced charges including two swiss franc 
