<TEXT>
the pound surged to an 18month high tuesday on 
continuing speculation that britain would soon join europes 
currencysteadying exchange rate mechanism 
the british government is trying to talk up sterling to fight 
inflation and bring the currency into the mechanism at a high 
level analysts said 
the exchange rate mechanism known as erm is built into the 
european monetary system and limits the fluctuations of nine of the 
12 european community currencies britain portugal and greece are 
the outsiders 
joining the mechanism would reduce sterlings volatility and 
help curb inflation the systems proponents say 
the pound which moved higher during the day finished at 
18155 in europe late tuesday up 1 cent from late monday that 
was the pounds highest level since it finished at 18270 on jan 
3 1989 
buying was extremely heavy dealers said 
there has been a lot of good solid investment demand for 
sterling said geoffrey dennis an economist at the london 
investment firm james capel and co 
the pound has gained 215 cents or 13 percent since midmarch 
when it fetched 16005 it also has risen strongly against the 
german mark and the japanese yen 
analysts predicted sterlings fourmonth climb is likely to 
continue 
the pound has quite a lot of room on the upside especially 
against the dollar said paul chertkow chief currency strategist 
at citibank in london dennis said the pound could fetch as much as 
187 in coming weeks chertkow expects it to reach 190 within 
three months 
the pound also has been sustained by britains 15 percent 
interest rates which are nearly double west germanys and are 
designed to fight inflation now running at 97 percent 
speculation about entry into the erm has gotten more and more 
intense dennis said in a series of comments statements 
speeches announcements the government gradually has dripfed the 
market information to encourage them to believe that sterling is 
going to join 
they have talked up the pound specifically to get it at a 
certain level at which they would like to join he continued 
it takes away the downside for sterling 
the pound got an added boost from britains top treasury 
official chancellor of the exchequer john major who said monday 
that the pounds climb was sustainable and that no interest rate 
cuts were planned 
inflation must improve before interest rates come down major 
told reporters at the group of seven meeting of major 
industrialized nations in houston 
he reiterated that britain wouldnt join the mechanism until 
britains inflation is more in line with the european communitys 
that is the major outstanding condition outlined by prime 
minister margaret thatcher who has committed britain to joining 
but has not set a timetable 
analysts expect mrs thatcher to link the pound to the erm in 
the autumn well before the next general election which must be 
called by mid1992 but could come in a year 
the government says that excluding mortgage rates inflation is 
7 percent and closer to the ecs average of 5 percent 
the government is believed to want to enter the mechanism with a 
strong pound so that britain can cut interest rates before voters 
go to the polls 
a stronger pound in effect adds up to tighter monetary policy 
it fights inflation by making it difficult for companies to grant 
wage increases and forcing them to keep down costs to retain export 
markets 
but a strong pound increases pressure on companies already 
struggling with high interest rates stock traders said 
british stocks have fallen in recent days amid concern that the 
pounds rise would hurt british exports and corporate profits 
