wasnt on anyones agenda 
his private investment firm boone co owns 26 percent of koito 
manufacturing co a japanese auto parts maker pickens 
unsuccessfully has tried to gain a voice in the company by landing 
four of koitos 20 board seats 
pickens claims he has been shut out of koito by japans 
keiretsu system in which companies have formed closed links 
through shared stock financial and personnel links and corporate 
strategies he alleges koito is part of the keiretsu surrounding 
toyota motor co which is its second largest shareholder and the 
largest buyer of its parts 
at a june 28 koito shareholders meeting pickens was denied 
board seats and was defeated on other proposals including larger 
dividends and having shareholders vote on salary and retirement 
benefits for board members 
koito claims pickens is trying to greenmail the company into 
buying his stock at premium prices company officials also contend 
pickens is acting on behalf of japanese investor kitaro watanabe 
who they say has twice tried to greenmail them 
when asked if he was in houston seeking the help of japanese 
prime minister toshiki kaifu pickens replied 
theres no doubt about it he could help my cause if he put 
any pressure on the toyotakoito group and said put the guy on 
the board and lets see if he would be a good board member sure i 
would like to see that call made by kaifu but i dont have any way 
to apply that kind of pressure 
pickens said he is more determined to buck the japanese system 
since being told remember pearl harbor and yankee go home 
at koitos annual shareholders meeting last month 
it was very shocking to me to go to a meeting where you own 26 
percent of the company and be told things like that he said 
its obvious the way they feel towards americans they dont want 
anyone seeing how they run their business 
